  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Build Coordinated Humanitarian Emergency Assessment Capacities in Afghanistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will build capacities for coordinated humanitarian emergency needs assessment using common tools for emergency response as well as soft skills for management and coordination of joint assessments, needs analysis and reporting, and protection sensitivity.

Capacity development on coordinated humanitarian needs assessments using the Humanitarian Coordinated Assessment Working Group (HCAWG)-approved common tool will be delivered through 15 national and regional trainings by three leading INGO partners of the Emergency Response Mechanism (ERM): Danish Committee for Aid to Afghan Refugees (DACAAR), Danish Refugee Council (DRC), and Norwegian Refugee Council (NRC), as well as ToT material development and capacity development for dealing with large-scale emergencies.</narrative>
  </description>
